  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased capacity building programmes, tools and city reports to assist Member States Member States, local authorities and key stakeholders to effectively promote tolerance and inclusion, and combat racism and discrimination</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a contribution to the commitment of Agenda 2030 to Leave No One Behind and with the view to create inclusive and rights-based societies, UNESCO will: 1) design and implement regional initiatives that combat racism and discrimination through targeted capacity building programmes and practical tools; 2) assist local governments to produce city reports with the aim to understand the various forms of discrimination; 3) develop a global learning package on how to apply HRBA across the specific areas of UNESCO&apos;s mandate accompanied by e-learning and MOOC versions. For the Slave Route project, capacity building will be developed and offered to institutions, communities and individuals to enhance their capacities to heal, preserve, promote and manage the slave trade heritage.</narrative>
  </description>
